IMO, this line in ContentManager is fairly unhelpful:

https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Content/ContentManager.cs#L315

``` csharp
if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(assetName))
{
    throw new ContentLoadException("Could not load " + originalAssetName + " asset as a non-content file!", ex);
}
```

It just covers up the original exception (unless you look at `InnerException`, but not everyone knows to do that).

If the non-content fallback file can't be found, couldn't we just re-throw the original exception?
